Package grafiosch.common

Class EnumHelper

java.lang.Object
grafiosch.common.EnumHelper
public abstract class EnumHelper extends Object
Utility class for operations on Enum types, particularly those implementing the StableEnum interface. It provides methods for encoding and decoding EnumSets into bitmasks, checking for enum presence in a bitmask, and other enum-related helpers.

  • Method Details

    • encodeEnumSet

      public static <E extends Enum<E> & StableEnum> long encodeEnumSet(EnumSet<E> set)
      Encodes an EnumSet of StableEnum into a long bitmask. Each enum constant in the set corresponds to a bit in the long value. The position of the bit is determined by the byte value returned by StableEnum.getValue().
      Type Parameters:
      E - The enum type, which must extend Enum and implement StableEnum.
      Parameters:
      set - The EnumSet to encode.
      Returns:
      A long value representing the bitmask of the EnumSet.

    • decodeEnumSet

      public static <E extends Enum<E> & StableEnum> EnumSet<E> decodeEnumSet(Class<E> enumClass, long bitVector)
      Decodes a long bitmask into an EnumSet of a specified StableEnum class.
      Type Parameters:
      E - The enum type, which must extend Enum and implement StableEnum.
      Parameters:
      enumClass - The Class object of the enum type.
      bitVector - The long bitmask to decode.
      Returns:
      An EnumSet containing the enum constants corresponding to the set bits in the bitmask.

    • contains

      public static <E extends Enum<E> & StableEnum> boolean contains(E targetEnum, long bitVector)
      Checks if a specific StableEnum constant is present in a long bitmask.
      Type Parameters:
      E - The enum type, which must extend Enum and implement StableEnum.
      Parameters:
      targetEnum - The enum constant to check for.
      bitVector - The long bitmask.
      Returns:
      true if the enum constant is represented in the bitmask, false otherwise.

    • decode

      public static <E extends Enum<E> & StableEnum> EnumSet<E> decode(int encoded, Class<E> enumKlazz)
      Decodes an integer bitmask (presumably from older code where int was used) into an EnumSet of a specified StableEnum class. This method assumes ordinals map directly to bit positions (0 to 30 for int).
      Type Parameters:
      E - The enum type, which must extend Enum and implement StableEnum.
      Parameters:
      encoded - The integer bitmask to decode.
      enumKlazz - The Class object of the enum type.
      Returns:
      An EnumSet containing the enum constants corresponding to the set bits in the bitmask. Returns an empty set if no corresponding enum values are found for the set bits.

    • enumContainsNameAsString

      public static <E extends Enum<E>> E enumContainsNameAsString(String name, Class<E> enumKlazz)
      Finds an enum constant in a given enum class by its string name.
      Type Parameters:
      E - The enum type.
      Parameters:
      name - The string name of the enum constant.
      enumKlazz - The Class object of the enum type.
      Returns:
      The enum constant if found, or null if no constant matches the name.
